 <label>Table 1.7</label>
 <caption>
  <p>Basic reproduction numbers and herd immunity thresholds for selected vaccine-preventable viral diseases</p>
 </caption>
 <table frame="hsides" rules="groups">
  <thead>
   <tr>
    <th>Disease</th>
    <th>
     <italic>R</italic>
     <sub>0</sub>
    </th>
    <th>Herd immunity threshold (%)</th>
   </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
   <tr>
    <td>HIV/AIDS</td>
    <td>2–5</td>
    <td>–</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td>Influenza (1918 A/H1N1)</td>
    <td>2–3</td>
    <td>–</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td>Measles</td>
    <td>12–18</td>
    <td>83–94</td>
   </tr>
